tspan.tspan: USIs are the URL for the mass spectrometry world. A USI points to a Proteomics Exchange
Identifier (PXD...), a file, and a spectrum in that file. Additionally, a peptidoform can be added to the

text.tspan: end, note that many servers require the peptidoform and a global charge state for the peptidoform.
Chimeric peptidoforms (forming one compound peptidoform ion)

tspan.tspan: To add a description or metadata
Modifications are defined between square brackets '[mod]'.
Multiple definitions can be combined with a vertical line '|'
Amino acids are written as the standard IUPAC symbols. With O/U added as pyrolysine, and
selenocysteine. J/B/Z are ambiguous amino acids for I/L, N/D, and Q/E respectively. Lastly X is
added as any unknown amino acid. X is defined to have a mass of zero. So 'X[+435]' can be used

text.tspan: to indicate a mass gap of 435 Da.
